  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nYannick requested testing of the Airtable MCP connector to understand its capabilities. Manus performed comprehensive testing across 13 available tools, demonstrating successful operations on a real Project Tracker database including data retrieval, creation, updates, and deletion. The connector proved fully functional with capabilities for discovery, data manipulation, and schema management.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nTesting and evaluation of the Airtable connector as part of the yOS AI infrastructure to validate functionality and understand integration capabilities\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nComprehensive testing of all 13 Airtable MCP connector tools including listing bases/tables, retrieving project data, searching records, creating/updating/deleting test records, and exploring schema capabilities\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [test_report] Airtable Connector Test Report — Comprehensive report documenting all 13 tools, test results, and live data examples\n- [data_samples] Project Tracker Data — Retrieved real project data including design projects with photos, team members, and relationships\n- [capability_matrix] Feature Overview — Summary of discovery, retrieval, manipulation, and schema management capabilities\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Airtable connector validated as fully functional and ready for production use\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- All 13 tools functional\n- Complex data types handled properly\n- Batch operations up to 10 records supported\n- Rich metadata and relationships preserved\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Connector supports attachments with thumbnails\n- Linked records and collaborators work seamlessly\n- Schema discovery provides complete field information\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Consider integration patterns for yOS\n- Explore automation workflows with Airtable data\n- Document best practices for production usage\n---\nUID: pBn7Xwu64FHJEL0K9uznLD | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0123\n"
}